        <section>
          <marginalnote>Definitions</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>1</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>In this regulation:</sectiontext>
          <definition>
            <term>British Columbia Building Code</term>
            <def>means the British Columbia Building Code established under section 2 of the British Columbia Building Code Regulation, B.C. Reg. 295/98;</def>
          </definition>
          <definition>
            <term>building permit</term>
            <def>means a building permit granted to a person who qualifies for exemption under this regulation;</def>
          </definition>
          <definition>
            <term>Galiano Island Trust Area</term>
            <def>means the local trust area established for Galiano Island under the <actname>Islands Trust Act</actname>.</def>
          </definition>
          <hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 92/2000, s. 1.]</hnote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Exemption</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>2</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Subject to section 4, a person who owns property in the Galiano Islands Trust Area and who meets the exemption requirements listed in section 3 is exempt from the provisions of the British Columbia Building Code.</sectiontext>
          <hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 92/2000, s. 2.]</hnote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Requirements for exemption</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>3</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>The requirements for an exemption under section 2 are that</sectiontext>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>a</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>the projected building must be</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <subparagraph>
            <subparagraphnumber>i</subparagraphnumber>
            <subparagraphtext>a single-family dwelling which will be the principal residence of the person exempted when it is completed, or</subparagraphtext>
          </subparagraph>
          <subparagraph>
            <subparagraphnumber>ii</subparagraphnumber>
            <subparagraphtext>an accessory building to a building described in subparagraph (i),</subparagraphtext>
          </subparagraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>b</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>the person exempted must own the land on which the projected building is to be built,</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>c</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>the person exempted must build, or act as general contractor for, the projected building,</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>d</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>the building project must be in compliance with applicable zoning or building bylaws in force in the Galiano Island Trust Area,</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>e</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>the person exempted</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <subparagraph>
            <subparagraphnumber>i</subparagraphnumber>
            <subparagraphtext>must apply to the Capital Regional District for a building permit established under section 694 (1) of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>, and</subparagraphtext>
          </subparagraph>
          <subparagraph>
            <subparagraphnumber>ii</subparagraphnumber>
            <subparagraphtext>must not have been granted a building permit under the <actname>Local Government Act</actname> for building on another property within the Galiano Island Trust Area within the 5 years preceding the date of application under subparagraph (i) for the permit, and</subparagraphtext>
          </subparagraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>f</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>the person exempted must grant a covenant under section 219 of the <actname>Land Title Act</actname> in favour of the Capital Regional District.</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 92/2000, s. 3.]</hnote>
        </section>
